<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Malachi on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/</link><description>Recent content in Malachi on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Malachi 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="malachi-chapter-1">Malachi Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-yahveh-covenant">Conversational Yahveh Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>An Oracle from Yahveh to Israel Through Malachi&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="jacob-loved-more-than-esau">Jacob Loved More Than Esau&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:4.5pt; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh says,&lt;i> “I’ve loved you.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:4.5pt; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> But you ask, &lt;i>“What do you mean ‘loved us’?”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;i>“Wasn’t Esau Jacob’s brother? Yet I’ve loved Jacob &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and set Esau aside, made his hill country desolate, and left his inheritance for desert jackals.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Malachi 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="malachi-chapter-2">Malachi Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="warning-to-priests">Warning to Priests&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Priests, I’m talking to you. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>If you don’t get serious about honoring me, I’ll put a curse on you and even curse the blessings you receive. Actually, I already have, because you’re not taking me seriously. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’ll bring misfortune on your descendants and spatter your faces with the offal from your feasts. I’ll throw you out with it. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>You’ll find out that I’m the One that sent this commandment so my covenant with Levi can continue.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>My covenant with him gives life and peace. I gave it to him so he’d show me reverence, and he did &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and gave true instruction. He followed me in peace and goodness and turned people back from sin. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>A priest should preserve knowledge, and people should look to him for instruction because he’s a messenger from Yahveh of hosts. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But you’ve gone off-road and made people stumble with your instruction; you’ve corrupted my covenant with Levi. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v9" id="v9">&lt;sup class="verse-num">9&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So people despise you because you show favoritism in how you execute the Law.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                       &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Malachi 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="malachi-chapter-3">Malachi Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:4.5pt; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“I’m going to send my messenger to fix the road ahead of me. Then Yahveh you’re looking for will suddenly come to his Temple, the messenger of the covenant you delight in. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But who can endure it when he comes? Who can withstand his appearing? He’ll like a refiner’s fire and a fuller’s soap. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He’ll sit like a refiner that smelts and purifies &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>dross from&lt;i> silver. He’ll purify the Levites and refine them like gold and silver so they can present acceptable offerings. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then the offerings in Judah and Jerusalem will be pleasing to me&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;i>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Y&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/i>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> like before. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Malachi 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/malachi/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="malachi-chapter-4">Malachi Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="mal-313-18">Mal 3:13-18&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="the-day-of-the-lord">The Day of the LORD&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:4.5pt; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“The time’s coming when the arrogant people &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>you admire &lt;i>will be like stubble that burns up in a furnace—root, stem, and all. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But for you that respect me, goodness will rise up like the sun with healing in its wings. You’ll break out, jump around for joy, and run all over like calves let out of a stall. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>At the time I’m planning for, you’ll stomp on sinners like ashes&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;i>under your feet.    &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>